## Key highlights from the earnings call

1. The company reiterated its 2025 EBITDA growth guidance of low-single digit growth y/y. As per the company, 4Q'25 EBITDA would be driven by higher mobile revenue as consumer purchasing power is improving and pricing discipline is maintained in the industry. In addition, revenue contribution revenue from GPU-as-a-service to increase in 4Q and cost discipline would be maintained;
2. It expects mobile ARPU to trend upwards and expects ARPU to rise to IDR45-50k in the medium term;
3. The bulk of revenue from GPU-as-a-service for 2025 should be reflected in 4Q25. The company reiterated revenue from GPU as a service to be USD35m in 2025, with a 60% EBITDA margin;
4. It expects fibre asset monetisation to conclude during 4Q25. With fibre being a strategic asset, particularly in the context of AI adoption, the company wants to balance short-term and long-term objectives and ensure long-term value creation through fibre asset monetisation.
